039/**
040 * An immutable {@link Bindings} containing {@link Qualifier}
041 * instances.
042 *
043 * <p>This is a <a
044 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based</a>
045 * class.</p>
046 *
047 * @param <V> the type of a {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
048 * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
049 *
050 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson"
051 * target="_parent">Laird Nelson</a>
052 *
053 * @see Bindings
054 */
055public final class Qualifiers<V> extends Bindings<V, Qualifier<V>> {
056
057
058  /*
059   * Static fields.
060   */
061
062
063  private static final Qualifiers<?> EMPTY = new Qualifiers<>(List.of());
064
065
066  /*
067   * Constructors.
068   */
069
070
071  private Qualifiers(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<V>> qualifiers) {
072    super(qualifiers);
073  }
074
075
076  /*
077   * Instance methods.
078   */
079
080
081  /**
082   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} with
083   * this {@link Qualifiers}' entries and an additional entry
084   * consisting of the supplied {@link Qualifier}.
085   *
086   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
087   * unless {@code qualifier} is {@code null}, in which case {@code
088   * this} will be returned.</p>
089   *
090   * @param qualifier a {@link Qualifier}; may be {@code null} in
091   * which case {@code this} will be returned
092   *
093   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with this {@link Qualifiers}'
094   * entries and an additional entry consisting of the supplied {@link
095   * Qualifier}
096   *
097   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
098   *
099   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
100   *
101   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
102   * threads.
103   *
104   * @see #plus(Iterable)
105   */
106  public final Qualifiers<V> plus(final Qualifier<V> qualifier) {
107    if (qualifier == null) {
108      return this;
109    } else if (this.isEmpty()) {
110      return of(qualifier);
111    } else {
112      return this.plus(List.of(qualifier));
113    }
114  }
115
116  /**
117   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} with
118   * this {@link Qualifiers}' entries and additional entries
119   * represented by the supplied {@code qualifiers}.
120   *
121   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
122   * unless {@code qualifier} is {@code null}, in which case {@code
123   * this} will be returned.</p>
124   *
125   * @param qualifiers additional {@link Qualifier}s; may be {@code
126   * null} in which case {@code this} will be returned
127   *
128   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with this {@link Qualifiers}'
129   * entries and additional entries represented by the supplied {@code
130   * qualifiers}
131   *
132   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
133   *
134   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
135   *
136   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
137   * threads.
138   */
139  public final Qualifiers<V> plus(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<V>> qualifiers) {
140    if (qualifiers == null) {
141      return this;
142    } else if (this.isEmpty()) {
143      return of(qualifiers);
144    }
145    final Collection<Qualifier<V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
146    for (final Qualifier<V> q : this) {
147      newQualifiers.add(q);
148    }
149    for (final Qualifier<V> q : qualifiers) {
150      newQualifiers.add(q);
151    }
152    return of(newQualifiers);
153  }
154
155  /**
156   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
157   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
158   * keys} are prefixed with the supplied {@code prefix}.
159   *
160   * <p>If this {@link Qualifiers} is {@linkplain #isEmpty() empty},
161   * then {@code this} is returned.</p>
162   *
163   * @param prefix a prefix; if {@code null} then {@code this} will be returned
164   *
165   * @return a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
166   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
167   * keys} are prefixed with the supplied {@code prefix}
168   *
169   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
170   *
171   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
172   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
173   *
174   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
175   * threads
176   */
177  public final Qualifiers<V> withPrefix(final String prefix) {
178    if (prefix == null || this.isEmpty()) {
179      return this;
180    }
181    return this.withPrefix(q -> prefix + q.name());
182  }
183
184  /**
185   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
186   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
187   * keys} are produced by the supplied {@link Function}, which is
188   * expected to prepend a prefix to the original key and return the
189   * result.
190   *
191   * <p>If this {@link Qualifiers} is {@linkplain #isEmpty() empty},
192   * then {@code this} is returned.</p>
193   *
194   * @param f a deterministic, idempotent {@link Function} that
195   * accepts keys drawn from this {@link Qualifiers}' {@link
196   * Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute keys}
197   * and returns a non-{@code null} prefixed version of that key; may
198   * be {@code null} in which case {@code this} will be returned
199   *
200   * @return a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
201   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
202   * keys} have been prefixed by the actions of the supplied {@link
203   * Function}
204   *
205   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
206   *
207   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
208   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
209   *
210   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
211   * threads, assuming the supplied {@link Function} is
212   */
213  public final Qualifiers<V> withPrefix(final Function<? super Qualifier<V>, ? extends String> f) {
214    if (f == null || this.isEmpty()) {
215      return this;
216    }
217    final Collection<Qualifier<V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
218    for (final Qualifier<V> q : this) {
219      newQualifiers.add(Qualifier.of(f.apply(q),
220                                     q.value(),
221                                     q.attributes(),
222                                     q.info()));
223    }
224    return of(newQualifiers);
225  }
226
227  /**
228   * Returns a {@link MethodHandleDesc} describing the constructor or
229   * {@code static} method that will be used to create a <a
230   * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/invoke/package-summary.html#condycon">dynamic
231   * constant</a> representing this {@link Qualifiers}.
232   *
233   * @return a {@link MethodHandleDesc} describing the constructor or
234   * {@code static} method that will be used to create a <a
235   * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/invoke/package-summary.html#condycon">dynamic
236   * constant</a> representing this {@link Qualifiers}
237   *
238   * @nullability This method does not, and its overrides must not,
239   * return {@code null}.
240   *
241   * @idempotency This method is, and its overrides must be,
242   * idempotent and deterministic.
243   *
244   * @threadsafety This method is, and its overrides must be, safe for
245   * concurrent use by multiple threads.
246   */
247  @Override // Bindings<V, Qualifier<V>>
248  protected final MethodHandleDesc describeConstructor() {
249    return
250      MethodHandleDesc.ofMethod(STATIC,
251                                CD_Qualifiers,
252                                "of",
253                                MethodTypeDesc.of(CD_Qualifiers, CD_Iterable));
254  }

262  /**
263   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
264   * created, whose {@link #isEmpty() isEmpty()} method will return
265   * {@code true}.
266   *
267   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
268   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}

271   *

274   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
275   *
276   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
277   * threads.
278   */
279  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
280  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of() {
281    return (Qualifiers<V>)EMPTY;
282  }

284  /**
285   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
286   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
287   *
288   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
289   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
290   *
291   * @param qualifier the sole {@link Qualifier} the {@link
292   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
293   *
294   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
295   *
296   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code qualifier} is {@code
297   * null}
298   *
299   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
300   *
301   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
302   *
303   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
304   * threads.
305   */
306  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of(final Qualifier<V> qualifier) {
307    return of(List.of(Objects.requireNonNull(qualifier, "qualifier")));
308  }

310  /**
311   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
312   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
313   *
314   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
315   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
316   *
317   * @param qualifier0 the first {@link Qualifier} the {@link
318   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
319   *
320   * @param qualifier1 the second {@link Qualifier} the {@link
321   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
322   *
323   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
324   *
325   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code qualifier} is {@code
326   * null}
327   *
328   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
329   *
330   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
331   *
332   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
333   * threads.
334   */
335  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of(final Qualifier<V> qualifier0, final Qualifier<V> qualifier1) {
336    return of(List.of(qualifier0, qualifier1));
337  }
338
339  /**
340   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
341   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
342   *
343   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
344   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
345   *
346   * @param qualifiers an {@link Iterable} representing {@link
347   * Qualifier} instances the {@link Qualifiers} will contain; may be
348   * {@code null}
349   *
350   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
351   *
352   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
353   *
354   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
355   *
356   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
357   * threads.
358   */
359  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<V>> qualifiers) {
360    if (qualifiers == null) {
361      return of();
362    }
363    final Iterator<? extends Qualifier<V>> i = qualifiers.iterator();
364    if (i.hasNext()) {
365      final Collection<Qualifier<V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
366      newQualifiers.add(i.next());
367      while (i.hasNext()) {
368        newQualifiers.add(i.next());
369      }
370      return new Qualifiers<>(newQualifiers);
371    }
372    return of();
373  }
374
375  /**
376   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
377   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
378   *
379   * @param qualifier0 the first {@link Qualifier} the {@link
380   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
381   *
382   * @param qualifier1 the second {@link Qualifier} the {@link
383   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
384   *
385   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
386   *
387   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code qualifier} is {@code
388   * null}
389   *
390   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
391   *
392   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
393   *
394   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
395   * threads.
396   */
397  public static final Qualifiers<?> ofDisparate(final Qualifier<?> qualifier0, final Qualifier<?> qualifier1) {
398    return ofDisparate(List.of(qualifier0, qualifier1));
399  }
400
401
402  /**
403   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
404   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
405   *
406   * @param qualifiers an {@link Iterable} representing {@link
407   * Qualifier} instances the {@link Qualifiers} will contain; may be
408   * {@code null}
409   *
410   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
411   *
412   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
413   *
414   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
415   *
416   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
417   * threads.
418   */
419  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
420  public static final Qualifiers<?> ofDisparate(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<?>> qualifiers) {
421    if (qualifiers == null) {
422      return of();
423    }
424    final Iterator<? extends Qualifier<?>> i = qualifiers.iterator();
425    if (i.hasNext()) {
426      final Collection<Qualifier<Object>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
427      newQualifiers.add((Qualifier<Object>)i.next());
428      while (i.hasNext()) {
429        newQualifiers.add((Qualifier<Object>)i.next());
430      }
431      return new Qualifiers<>(newQualifiers);
432    }
433    return of();
434  }
